headline: Costco’s (COST) Membership Model Powers Ouperformance as Headwinds Persist
summary: Costco’s (COST) fiscal Q3 2025 results show the retail giant remains largely insulated from broader economic pressures, thanks to the loyalty of its massive member base. Revenue grew 8% year-over-year, outpacing competitors such as Target (TGT) and Walmart (WMT), despite challenges including inflation and tariffs. The key driver? headline: The Zacks Analyst Blog Highlights Costco Wholesale, Walmart and Amazon.com
summary: COST joins the BNPL race with Affirm, aiming to boost big-ticket e-commerce sales and compete with AMZN and WMT.
